Headlines.Headline: BEFORE THE BELL: US Stock Futures Rise After China Data

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Polya Lesova FRANKFURT (MarketWatch)--U.S. stock futures posted solid gains on Friday, while the U.S. dollar fell against major rivals and gold gained, and as strong economic data from China encouraged appetite for assets perceived as risky. Futures on the Dow Jones Industrial Average advanced 54 points to 10,777 and S&P 500 futures rose 6.20 points to 1,142.90. Nasdaq 100 futures added 13 points to 2,008.50. U.S. stocks ended lower on Thursday, but the blue-chip Dow index gained 7.7% last month, posting its best September performance since 1939 when it rose 13.5%.

PARAGRAPH.#text: (This article was originally published Thursday.) NEW YORK (Dow Jones)--A recent move by U.S. regulators means more paperwork for companies emitting greenhouse gases.
